J.Q Patisserie Artisan French Pastries, Handcrafted with Love Kluang, Johor, Malaysia About Us J.Q Patisserie is a boutique pastry shop dedicated to the art of French baking. Founded with a passion for authentic patisserie, we bring the elegance and craftsmanship of traditional French techniques to the heart of Kluang, Johor. Every pastry that leaves our kitchen is handcrafted using premium ingredients sourced for quality — from imported French butter to Belgian chocolate. We believe that exceptional pastries are created through patience, precision, and an unwavering commitment to excellence. Whether you're celebrating a special milestone, treating yourself to an afternoon indulgence, or looking for the perfect gift, J.Q Patisserie promises an unforgettable experience in every bite. Our Philosophy Quality Without Compromise We use only the finest ingredients: French butter for our croissants, Valrhona chocolate for our ganaches, and fresh seasonal fruits for our tarts. No shortcuts, no compromises. Artisan Craftsmanship Every pastry is handmade in small batches. Our croissant dough is laminated over 48 hours, our cakes are assembled with meticulous care, and our decorations are crafted by hand. Freshness Guaranteed We bake fresh daily. What you see in our display is made that morning, ensuring you always enjoy our pastries at their absolute best. Our Specialties Signature Croissants — Our butter croissants are crafted using a traditional 48-hour lamination process, resulting in perfectly flaky, golden layers with a buttery aroma. Burnt Basque Cheesecake — A customer favourite! Creamy, caramelized, and utterly indulgent. Available in whole cakes and slices. French Tarts — From classic Tarte au Citron to seasonal fruit tarts, each features a crisp, buttery shell and luscious fillings. Custom Celebration Cakes — Bespoke cakes designed for birthdays, weddings, anniversaries, and corporate events. Every creation is unique.

J.Q PATISSERIE Customer Guide & Frequently Asked Questions Welcome to J.Q Patisserie! This guide answers our most commonly asked questions to help you with ordering, custom cakes, and more. General Questions Q: Where is J.Q Patisserie located? A: We''re located at No. 23, Jalan Mawar 3, Taman Bunga Raya, 86000 Kluang, Johor, Malaysia. Look for the cream-coloured shophouse with our signature brown logo! Q: What are your operating hours? A: Tuesday to Friday: 10:00 AM - 7:00 PM | Saturday & Sunday: 9:00 AM - 8:00 PM | Monday: CLOSED. Hours may vary on public holidays — check our Instagram for updates. Q: Do I need to make a reservation to visit? A: No reservation needed for walk-ins! However, popular items sell out quickly, especially on weekends. For guaranteed availability, we recommend pre-ordering. Q: Is parking available? A: Yes, free street parking is available directly in front of our shop and along Jalan Mawar. Ordering & Pre-Orders Q: How do I place a pre-order? A: WhatsApp us at +60 12-345 6789 with your order details. For regular pastries, order at least 1 day in advance. For custom cakes, minimum 3 days advance notice is required. Q: What payment methods do you accept? A: We accept Cash, Credit/Debit Cards, Touch ''n Go eWallet, GrabPay, and DuitNow QR. Bank transfer is also available for pre-orders. Q: Do you require a deposit for custom cakes? A: Yes, we require a 50% deposit to confirm your custom cake order. The remaining balance is payable upon collection. Q: Can I cancel or modify my order? A: Orders can be modified up to 48 hours before the collection date. Cancellations made less than 48 hours in advance may forfeit the deposit as ingredients would have been purchased. Products & Menu Q: What is your specialty? A: We''re known for our Burnt Basque Cheesecake, handcrafted croissants (48-hour laminated dough!), and French tarts. Our macarons and custom celebration cakes are also customer favourites.
